FBIS3-36841 "drsov028_d_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 Regional Affairs Chechen Opposition Figure Detained in Groznyy LD1002130494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 10 Feb 94 LD1002130494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Major General Ibragim Suleymenov, a Chechen opposition leader, and several of his colleagues have been detained in the center of Groznyy, Sultan Geliskhanov, chief of the State Security Department of Chechnya told INTERFAX. A large quantity of weapons -- including two grenade launchers, four sub-machine guns, ammunition, narcotics, and counterfeit money -- were confiscated from Suleymenov's group. The detainees are being held at a State Security Department remand center.
